17:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Salesforce Flow is best suited for Salesforce admins, enterprises, sales operations, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Zoho Flow, meanwhile, shines for Zoho users, small businesses, budget conscious teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 1999, Salesforce Flow describes itself as \"Salesforce's declarative automation engine for complex business processes.\" Zoho Flow, established in 1996, positions itself as \"Integration platform connecting Zoho and third-party apps with automated workflows.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
18:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Salesforce Flow** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), more features (10 vs 9). However, this does not mean Zoho Flow is a poor choice — far from it. Zoho Flow excels in its own right, particularly for Zoho users and small businesses.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value extremely powerful for salesforce automation, go with Salesforce Flow. If excellent value within zoho ecosystem matters more to you, Zoho Flow is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
